'<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
'For the purpose of the aforementioned project, our Engineering Agency, at the request of the Client, issues a structural advice in this report.
'This report is carried out under our general terms and conditions (which can be sent upon request) and the DNR 2011.

'<h2>2. Project Description</h2>
'The project involves a structural advice for the Portakabin modular building system.

'<img style="width:100%;" src="./Images/Picture0.png" alt="Picture0.png">

'<h2>3. Structure</h2>
'<h3>3.1 Explanation of the Building System</h3>
'A movable PORTA KABIN building system is a construction system where units are connected in a single row and can be placed up to two stories high.
  'Below we see the configuration used in this project.

#val
'The building contains <b>'n_story' levels </b> 
#equ

drawGeneral$(b; l; n_Length)
'The PORTA KABIN modules are intended for non-permanent use. See the attachment with the KOMO certificate.
'These modules are available in the dimensions listed below:
#val
'<table style="width: 100%;" class="table">
'  <tr><th>Parameters</th><th>Values</th></tr>
'  <tr><td>External length (m)</td><td>'l'</td></tr>
'  <tr><td>External width (m)</td><td>'b'</td></tr>
'  <tr><td>Total height (m)</td><td>'h'</td></tr>
'  <tr><td>Floor level relative to foundation (m)</td><td>'l_floor'</td></tr>
'  <tr><td>Empty weight of the unit (kN)</td><td>'G_unit'</td></tr>
'  <tr><td>Number of intermediate supports for ground floor</td><td>'n_Int,support,points'</td></tr>
'</table>
#equ

'<h3>3.2 Points of attention during execution</h3>
'Prior to placing the foundation plates: check the subsoil for organic soil layers.

'The module is constructed from a steel structure that provides strength and stability. The calculation for this is not included in this report. Based on the KOMO certificate, it is suitable for use with a variable load of 3-5 kN/m┬▓. Please see the attached KOMO certificate for more information.
'
'One module consists of a steel frame with tubular profiles. The floor is made up of a wooden beam structure. Stability is ensured by the moment-resistant connections in two directions within the steel frame.

'<h3>3.3 Foundation</h3>
'The building is a temporary structure with a short reference period. It is also a serially produced simple product, of which hundreds have already been built.

'<b>The construction falls under geotechnical category 1 according to the EC7.</b>
'Quote from NEN 9997-1 Geotechnical design of structures
'<i>
'14) Geotechnical category 1 should only include small and relatively simple structures:
'
'for which it can be ensured, based on experience and qualitative geotechnical investigation that,
'<ul>
'  <li>the fundamental requirements are met</li>
'  <li>with negligible risk</li>
'</ul>
'
'15) The procedures of geotechnical category 1 should only be used if there is a negligible risk with regard to overall stability or ground deformations and a subsoil condition that, based on other local experience, is known to be sufficiently uncomplicated. In these cases, the procedures may consist of routine methods for the design and execution of the foundation.
'

'16) The procedures of geotechnical category 1 should only be used if no excavation takes place below the groundwater level or if, based on comparable local experience, it is known that the proposed excavation below the groundwater level can be carried out without issues.
'Building and ground structures may be classified in geotechnical category 1 provided the following criteria a to c are met:
'<h6>a. Type and size of the structure:</h6>
'<b>(1) Permitted are light structures:</b>
' - with a design load value on the foundation strips of up to 100 kN/m and on slabs or footings of up to 250 kN;
' - with a design floor load value of up to 20 kN/m┬▓;
' - equipped with foundation structures whose behavior has been tested based on local experience;
' - equipped with a foundation on wooden or prefabricated concrete piles that are only subjected to vertical compression, and for which a pile driving log has been created for each pile over at least the last 2 meters of penetration, confirming that the piles are situated in the load-bearing layer.
'<h6>b. Influences from the surrounding:</h6>
'Environmental influences are so minor that the behavior of the structures mentioned under a) can be determined using locally acquired knowledge.
'<h6>c. Deformations:</h6>
'No stringent requirements are imposed on the structure.
'</i>

'Based on the above, it is evident that a temporary POTA KABIN module is a structure in geotechnical category 1.
'Therefore, no geotechnical investigation was carried out in accordance with Article 3.1, paragraph 4a:
'a) Geotechnical investigation may be omitted if the structure is classified in geotechnical category 1, and if the following conditions are met:
'
' - The geological map shows a homogeneous soil composition;
' - The foundation of the structure is comparable to the foundation method used in adjacent plots, where, in the case of pile foundations, driven piles must have been used.

'Location: <b>'locationName$'</b>'
'Subsoil type: <b>'subsoilName$'</b>'
'Maximum pressure, <b>'p_soil'</b>'

